Front-end Process / CSS Architecture:

- All features / functionality start out as a base component with a set of base styles.
- There is one SCSS file per component.
- All unique modifications are made in an isolated section of that same SCSS file. (Not inline or in a jsx file).
- Use semantic naming conventions when defining uniques (page prefix, logical grouping, etc).

example:

<section class="hero ideas-hero">
  <div class="hero-main">
    <h1>stuff</h1>
    <button class="pill-button theme-green shadow">
      Heya
    </button>
  </div>
</section>

